  <div class="teaser-lg--main">

          <div class="teaser-lg__image">
          <a href="/us/blog/have-you-ever-wondered/202404/can-we-safety-proof-our-kids-brains-in-this-digital-age"><img loading="lazy" src="https://cdn2.psychologytoday.com/assets/styles/manual_crop_1_1_288x288/public/field_blog_entry_images/2024-04/TeensAtBeachOnCellphones.jpg?itok=vd50NxPN" width="288" height="288" alt="Digital interactions trump in-person social interaction." title="Andrea Piacquadio / Pexels" />

</a>

      </div>
    
    <div class="teaser-lg__details">
      
                        <div class="h2 teaser-lg__title">
            <a href="/us/blog/have-you-ever-wondered/202404/can-we-safety-proof-our-kids-brains-in-this-digital-age" rel="bookmark">Can We Safety-Proof Our Kids&#039; Brains in This Digital Age?</a>
          </div>
              
      
              <p class="teaser-lg__summary teaser-lg__teaser--desktop">
            Learn how to combat the overreliance on social media and digital communication for social interactions in our families and in our own lives.
      </p>
          </div>

  </div>

      <p class="teaser-lg__summary teaser-lg__teaser--mobile">
            Learn how to combat the overreliance on social media and digital communication for social interactions in our families and in our own lives.
      </p>
  </article>
</div>

    
    
